cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ACPM — Agent Capability and Profile Model (Schema Commons SC-014)"
message: "If you use ACPM, please cite it using these metadata."
type: dataset
abstract: >-
  ACPM is an open, vendor-neutral standard for describing what an AI agent,
  platform, tool, or model actually offers, independent of how it is run
  (SC-006 AAIF) or discovered (SC-013 AREG). It standardises the declaration
  of a capability profile — subject identity, dot-namespaced capability
  support levels, tool/model/memory inventories, trust and attestation
  posture, cost structure, SLA commitments, structured delegation rules,
  and compliance posture — so registries, marketplaces, and orchestrators
  can compare and match agents/platforms/tools/models without bespoke
  per-vendor parsing. It is published as JSON Schema 2020-12 plus a
  JSON-LD context.
keywords:
  - artificial intelligence
  - LLM agents
  - capability profile
  - trust and attestation
  - interoperability
  - open standard
  - JSON Schema
  - service catalog
